HEADWORD: Cladocera
<hw>Cla*doc"e*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ a sprout + <?/ a horn.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order
of the Entomostraca.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ They have a bivalve shell, covering the body but not the
head, and from four to six pairs of legs and two pairs of anten⟦ae⟧, for
use in swimming. They mostly inhabit fresh water.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cladode</ent>⟦br⟧
